6971inline bool Type::isIntegerType() const {
6972 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
6973 return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::Bool &&
6974 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::Int128;
6975 if (const EnumType *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType)) {
6976 // Incomplete enum types are not treated as integer types.
6977 // FIXME: In C++, enum types are never integer types.
6978 return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl()) &&
6979 !IsEnumDeclScoped(ET->getDecl());
6980 }
6981 return isExtIntType();
6982}

7010 return ((BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortAccum &&
7011 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::LongAccum) ||
7012 (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortFract &&
7013 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::LongFract) ||
7014 (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortAccum &&
7015 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatLongAccum) ||
7016 (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortFract &&
7017 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatLongFract));
7018 }

7026inline bool Type::isScalarType() const {
7027 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
7028 return BT->getKind() > BuiltinType::Void &&
7029 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::NullPtr;
7030 if (const EnumType *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType))
7031 // Enums are scalar types, but only if they are defined. Incomplete enums
7032 // are not treated as scalar types.
7033 return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl());
7034 return isa<PointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7035 isa<BlockPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7036 isa<MemberPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7037 isa<ComplexType>(CanonicalType) ||
7038 isa<ObjCObjectPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7039 isExtIntType();
7040}

7042inline bool Type::isIntegralOrEnumerationType() const {
7043 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
7044 return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::Bool &&
7045 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::Int128;
7046
7047 // Check for a complete enum type; incomplete enum types are not properly an
7048 // enumeration type in the sense required here.
7049 if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType))
7050 return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl());

7052 return isExtIntType();

7137// Helper class template that is used by Type::getAs to ensure that one does
7138// not try to look through a qualified type to get to an array type.
7139template <typename T>
7140using TypeIsArrayType =
7141 std::integral_constant<bool, std::is_same<T, ArrayType>::value ||
7142 std::is_base_of<ArrayType, T>::value>;
7143
7144// Member-template getAs<specific type>'.
7145template <typename T> const T *Type::getAs() const {
7146 static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value,
7147 "ArrayType cannot be used with getAs!");
7148
7149 // If this is directly a T type, return it.
7150 if (const auto *Ty = dyn_cast<T>(this))
7151 return Ty;
7152
7153 // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
7154 if (!isa<T>(CanonicalType))
7155 return nullptr;
7156
7157 // If this is a typedef for the type, strip the typedef off without
7158 // losing all typedef information.
7159 return cast<T>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7160}
7161
7162template <typename T> const T *Type::getAsAdjusted() const {
7163 static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value, "ArrayType cannot be used with getAsAdjusted!");
7164
7165 // If this is directly a T type, return it.
7166 if (const auto *Ty = dyn_cast<T>(this))
7167 return Ty;
7168
7169 // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
7170 if (!isa<T>(CanonicalType))
7171 return nullptr;
7172
7173 // Strip off type adjustments that do not modify the underlying nature of the
7174 // type.
7175 const Type *Ty = this;
7176 while (Ty) {
7177 if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Ty))
7178 Ty = A->getModifiedType().getTypePtr();
7179 else if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<ElaboratedType>(Ty))
7180 Ty = E->desugar().getTypePtr();
7181 else if (const auto *P = dyn_cast<ParenType>(Ty))
7182 Ty = P->desugar().getTypePtr();
7183 else if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<AdjustedType>(Ty))
7184 Ty = A->desugar().getTypePtr();
7185 else if (const auto *M = dyn_cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Ty))
7186 Ty = M->desugar().getTypePtr();
7187 else
7188 break;
7189 }
7190
7191 // Just because the canonical type is correct does not mean we can use cast<>,
7192 // since we may not have stripped off all the sugar down to the base type.
7193 return dyn_cast<T>(Ty);
7194}
7195
7196inline const ArrayType *Type::getAsArrayTypeUnsafe() const {
7197 // If this is directly an array type, return it.
7198 if (const auto *arr = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(this))
7199 return arr;
7200
7201 // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
7202 if (!isa<ArrayType>(CanonicalType))
7203 return nullptr;
7204
7205 // If this is a typedef for the type, strip the typedef off without
7206 // losing all typedef information.
7207 return cast<ArrayType>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7208}
7209
7210template <typename T> const T *Type::castAs() const {
7211 static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value,
7212 "ArrayType cannot be used with castAs!");
7213
7214 if (const auto *ty = dyn_cast<T>(this)) return ty;
7215 assert(isa<T>(CanonicalType));
7216 return cast<T>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7217}
7218
7219inline const ArrayType *Type::castAsArrayTypeUnsafe() const {
7220 assert(isa<ArrayType>(CanonicalType));
7221 if (const auto *arr = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(this)) return arr;
7222 return cast<ArrayType>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7223}
